## 5. Market Analysis

- **Industry size and trends:** The global language services market is estimated at roughly $58B–$79B for 2025 depending on source (Mordor Intelligence ~$72B; Coherent ~$79B). The US Translation Services industry (IBISWorld, NAICS 54193) has grown at roughly 4.1% CAGR 2020–2025; forward global forecasts run 5–9% CAGR. Translation contributes ~43% and interpretation ~32% of category revenue.
- **Growth drivers and barriers:** Drivers — rising demand for healthcare, legal, and government language access; immigration-driven demand for less-common languages; globalization of commercial clients. Barriers / headwinds — AI machine translation and AI-enabled localization are compressing pricing on commodity translation work; interpretation (especially rare languages, legal/medical settings) is more defensible against AI substitution.
- **Competitive landscape (peer benchmarks):**
  - LanguageLine Solutions / large national LSPs — enterprise-scale phone & video remote interpreting; set price floors on commodity work.
  - Regional LSPs (e.g., ALTA Language Services, Atlanta) — mid-market commercial/government accounts; comparable service breadth.
  - Small independent translation/interpreting firms — the target's peer set; typically trade in the 2.5x–4.0x SDE range for sub-$1M-SDE deals.

