## 9. Risk Factors

- **Industry-specific risks:** AI/machine translation is eroding pricing on commodity written translation; the interpretation mix (especially rare languages and regulated settings) is more defensible — confirm the translation-vs-interpretation revenue split.
- **Financial risks:** Thin 13.2% SDE margin; unknown customer concentration; no multi-year trend to confirm stability or growth. True normalized EBITDA is likely below SDE once a market GM salary is deducted, raising the effective entry multiple.
- **Operational risks:** Delivery almost certainly depends on a contracted linguist network — retention of key interpreters and worker-classification (1099 vs W-2) compliance are material. GM is the operational linchpin; confirm a retention/transition arrangement.
- **Regulatory / legal:** Court and healthcare interpreting may require certified interpreters (state court certification, medical interpreter credentials) — confirm credentialed-linguist coverage. 1099 classification exposure under federal/state labor rules.
- **Deal-specific conditions:**
  - **UNDER CONTRACT** — the deal is not actionable today. Pursue only as a backup offer or if the pending transaction collapses. Confirm with the broker whether a backup-offer position is being accepted.
  - Multiple is on SDE, not normalized EBITDA — re-underwrite at a market GM salary; if the effective EBITDA multiple exceeds 4.0x, negotiate price down as a closing condition.
  - Obtain 3–5 years of P&Ls and tax returns to verify the 3-year revenue/profit-growth and 10-year-tenure checks before committing time.

